---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Methodology · State of AI Code Review"
  description="How the data was produced. Source, filters, privacy thresholds, reproducibility, and consent."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20 pb-12">
    <p class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent-500 mb-6">Methodology</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-medium tracking-tight leading-[1.05]">
      How the data was produced.
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pb-16 space-y-12 leading-relaxed text-ink-700">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-4">Source</h2>
      <p>
        All data is sourced from the Kodus production code review pipeline. Kodus reviews pull requests across GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, and Azure DevOps. The full dataset lives in a BigQuery warehouse. Each chart in this report has a backing SQL query published in the <a href="https://github.com/kodustech/stateofcodereview.com" class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:text-accent-700">GitHub repository</a> under <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-ink-100 px-1.5 py-0.5">methodology/queries/</code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-4">Engine cutoff: 2025-09-01</h2>
      <p>
        Kodus introduced a new label taxonomy in September 2025 with 5 canonical labels: bug, security, performance, cross-file, and kody rules. Suggestions generated before this cutoff used a different label set and a different LLM prompt. To keep findings interpretable as the current state of AI code review, all suggestions before 2025-09-01 are excluded.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-4">Privacy thresholds</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 space-y-2">
        <li>No slice with fewer than 50 suggestions is published as a finding.</li>
        <li>Programming language slices with fewer than 5 distinct organizations are footnoted as low-confidence.</li>
        <li>Organization, repository, and pull request identifiers are never exposed.</li>
        <li>Suggestion text shown in the report is reviewed for sensitive substrings (hostnames, customer identifiers, project names) before publication.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-4">Sample sizes (2026-Q2)</h2>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-200"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Suggestions with feedback (post-filter)</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">17,773</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-200"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Distinct organizations</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">200</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-200"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Distinct repositories</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">639</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-200"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Programming languages</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">103</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-200"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Bug findings</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">14,560</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-200"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Security findings</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">7,483</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-200"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Cross-file findings</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">1,852</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-ink-200"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Codified review rules</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">7,276</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">Organizations with codified rules</td><td class="py-2 font-mono text-right">610</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-4">What is not included</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 space-y-2">
        <li>Suggestions from Kodus self-hosted deployments. The data warehouse covers Cloud only.</li>
        <li>Suggestions without explicit developer feedback. Unobserved suggestions are excluded because reception cannot be measured.</li>
        <li>Pull requests from organizations that opted out of research. Reserved as policy. None currently.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-4">Consent and ethics</h2>
      <p>
        Organizations using Kodus consent to aggregated, anonymized research per the Terms of Service. No individually identifiable data is published. To validate findings against a controlled extract, contact <a href="mailto:research@kodus.io" class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:text-accent-700">research@kodus.io</a> under a data use agreement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-4">How to cite</h2>
      <p class="font-mono text-sm bg-ink-100 p-4 leading-relaxed">
        State of AI Code Review (2026-Q2). Research by Kodus.<br />
        https://stateofcodereview.com
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
